        outcome: "We located the split in a 3/4-inch copper supply line in the north-wall cavity, cut out the damaged 22-inch section, and replaced it with new copper with soldered fittings. We then wrapped the entire pipe run in that wall with foam pipe insulation and added electric heat tape rated to -20 degrees Fahrenheit. We also identified two other at-risk runs in the exterior garage wall and wrapped those proactively in the same visit. Total repair and winterization: three hours forty minutes.",
